I think a good way to not get burnt out coding and doing math 24/7 a day is to do some more creative work to break the monotony.
Or perhaps I am simply bad at saying &ldquo;No!&rdquo;
The moral of the story is that I took over makign the Taipan logo for the Taipan survey. The original art was all done in green, and I thought - given the lack of green colouring in many astronomical surveys, and given the snake is vaguely green(ish brown), sure, sounds good!
